data.value:
Preparation
• Stretch your core, hips, and lower back before starting.
• Find a flat, open space with enough room to move comfortably.
• Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat or slightly raised for more intensity.
• After pressing START, there’s a 4-second countdown before the challenge begins.
During the Challenge
• Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground (or raised for more challenge).
• Lean back slightly, keeping your spine straight and your core engaged.
• Hold your hands together in front of your chest, or if using a weight, hold it with both hands.
• Rotate your torso to the right, bringing your hands toward the floor beside your hip.
• Return to center and rotate to the left side, tapping the floor beside your hip.
• Keep your core tight and avoid swinging your arms; the movement should come from your torso.
• Maintain a steady pace for the entire 2 minutes.
Finishing the Challenge
• When done, enter the number of repetitions you completed in the REPS field, then press DONE.
Exercise Guide
• Sit with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground, or for a more advanced option, raise your feet off the ground.
• Lean back slightly, maintaining a straight back and engaged core.
• Twist your torso to the right, then back to the center, and twist to the left.
• Focus on using your core muscles to control the movement, not just your arms.
• Keep a steady pace and try not to rush; form is key to maximizing the benefits.
Note
Push yourself to maintain proper form for the entire 2 minutes challenge. Engage your core to prevent straining your back.
"Twist your way to a stronger core—one rep at a time!"
